stuff
=====

Here, I keep all configuration files, which are accessed by apps through
symbolic links generated by the install.sh script. To find out what it can do,
run it to see a help message.

Some features are provided by programs that need to be compiled. Makefiles
are in home/bin. You may need to edit home/bin/batlog.c and the Makefiles.


Apps and Packages
-----------------

- Necessary: Neovim Git GCC Make brightnessctl
- Apps: Alacritty Firefox Chrome Okular Thunderbird GIMP Inkscape LibreOffice
  Telegram-Desktop Celluloid simple-scan TeXStudio Apostrophe Strawberry
  simplescreenrecorder klavaro qpdfview-qt5 Thunar
- Utilities: TeXLive IPython mksh Rust Cargo Python
- Small systems: dmenu openbox tint2 picom feh pavucontrol clipmenu dunst xclip
  bluez{,-utils} pulseaudio-bluetooth CUPS sane openssh flatpak
- Minimal distros: libinput wpa_supplicant dhcp mesa-driver
  xorg{-server,-server-utils,-xinit} intel-driver libinput-driver zip unzip tar
  pulseaudio
- Dev work: libpulse pulseaudio-lib libX11{,-devel} libXft{,-devel}
  libXinerama{,-devel} libXrandr{,-devel}
- Studies: ROOT, Ostap
- KDE: packagekit{,-qt5} appstream{,-qt5} wl-clipboard latte-dock
- GNOME: dash-to-dock-ext. clipboard-ext. gnome-tweaks

Apps that may appear to be useful in the future:

- guvcview(-qt) -- capture video output in real time and even do something
  simple to it.
- exiftool -- show and edit files metadata.

The Special directory:
- Import okular.shortcuts in Okular Settings > Configure Keyboard Shortcuts
  > Manage Schemes > More Actions > Import Scheme.
- Copy 30-libinput.conf and 20-display.conf to /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/.
- If Firefox haven't taken care of the bookmarks, import them from
  bookmarks.html.

To use SDDM (or any other display manager):

    systemctl enable --now sddm.service
    systemctl set-default multi-user.target


Configure dnf:

    fastestmirror=1
    max_parallel_downloads=10


Create an ssh key and add it to GitHub and other services:

    ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
    # OR ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"

    GitHub: https://docs.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account

    GitLab: https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ssh/#adding-an-ssh-key-to-your-gitlab-account

Then change all git remotes to ssh

    git remote set-url origin ssh:git@[].git


Various Instructions
====================

GNOME configuration:
- Backup: dconf dump / > backup.conf
- Restore: dconf load / < backup.conf
- GNOME directory contains configuration to be restored.
- GNOME should also come with extensions, see notes.txt.


User and Group management:
- Add user: useradd -m name (-m creates /home/name)
- Add group: groupadd name
- Add user to a group: gpasswd -a user group (-d user to remove)
- Add a full name to a user: chfn full_name user


Network:
- Start dhcpcd: dhcpcd -q -w %I
- Stop dhcpcd: dhcpcd -x %I
- wpa_supplicant -c/etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant-%I.conf -i%I -B
- nm-online -s -q


Hissing sound in headphones... Google it if the problem ever comes up.


ArchLinux pacman usage:
- Info on an installed package: pacman -Qi package
- Search installed: pacman -Qs word
- Group members: pacman -Qg group
- List files from a package: pacman -Ql package
- Find the owner of a file: pacman -Qo file
- List unneeded dependency packages: pacman -Qdt
- Remove a package and its unneeded dependencies: pacman -Rs package
- Check if a package is needed and remove: pacman -Ru package
- Info: pacman -Si package (double i sometimes).
- Search packages: pacman -Ss word
- Perform a full system update: pacman -Syyu
- Clean cache with uninstalled packages: pacman -Sc
- Install a .pkg.tar.gz: pacman -U local.pkg.tar.gz
- Colored output: uncomment "#Color" in /etc/pacman.conf
- When there are signature trust problems:
  - Update gnupg,
  - Run pacman-key --refresh-keys


CUPS configuration:
- Install CUPS and enable + start org.cups.cupsd.service,
- Create a group named lpadmin,
- Edit SystemGroup line in /etc/cups/cups-files.conf â€“ add lpadmin,
- Add the user to group lpadmin,
- Type localhost:631/ in a browser,
- Add samba backend somehow if it is absent,
- Add printer smb://guest@192.168.1.1/Xerox3250,
  (the format is thing://guest@IP/name)
  you can run smbclient -L 192.168.1.1,
- Use driver ph3250.ppd. Check the Share checkbox.


Thunderbird configuration:
- CERN email configuration: Google it...
- The font types you need are: Cyrilic, Latin, Other Writing Systems. Set their
  sizes to 18.
